PML Macro file syntax
=====================

Each macro file (.mdf - macro definition file) is of the form:

The tags are the synonomous names for the macro. Each
macro must have at least one tag. The body of the
macro is enclosed by braces "{" and ""}.

# Optional comment 
tag_1
tag_2
tag_3
{   <macro command definition 1>
    <macro command definition 2>

    ...

    # Optional comment
    <macro command definition i>

    ...

    <macro command definition N>
}
